---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About — Zac Culpan"
  description="Zac Culpan is Head of Marketing at Narrative and incoming Head of Product at OneRoof (NZME). Writing about growth, ecosystem marketing, and creator strategies."
>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="post-header">
      <span class="post-tag">About</span>
      <img src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}zac-headshot-final.jpg`} alt="Zac Culpan" class="about-headshot" />
      <h1 class="post-title">Hi, I'm Zac.</h1>
      <p class="post-desc">Head of Marketing turning Head of Product. Writing about what I'm learning at the edge of growth, marketing, and product strategy.</p>
    </div>
    <article class="post-content">
      <p>I've spent my career at the intersection of marketing and product — figuring out what makes growth compound. Currently Head of Marketing at <a href="https://www.narrative.so" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Narrative</strong></a>, a SaaS startup, and moving into Head of Product at <a href="https://www.oneroof.co.nz" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>OneRoof</strong></a>, the real estate platform owned by NZME.</p>
      <p>On the side, I'm building a startup focused on ecosystem and creator marketing — helping companies grow through communities, partnerships, and creator-led channels rather than paid acquisition alone.</p>
      <h2>What I Write About</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Ecosystem marketing</strong> — why the next moat isn't features, it's networks</li>
        <li><strong>Creator marketing</strong> — what actually works, and what's just attention arbitrage</li>
        <li><strong>SaaS growth</strong> — frameworks for sustainable growth in B2B</li>
        <li><strong>Marketing → Product</strong> — what each discipline borrows from the other</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
      <p>The best place to reach me is <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/zachary-culpan/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>. Always happy to talk growth, creator marketing, or ecosystem strategies.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>